    "synopsis": "Born into the freezing dark of Nostramo, raised by no one, Konrad Curze pulled a planet of murderers into something like order through fear — and never recovered from what it cost him. The novel braids three strands of his life: the boyhood on Nostramo, his recovery after weeks adrift in deep space, and the final hours before his foretold death. In each, Curze relives the choices that turned a primarch into the Night Haunter, arguing with the absent father who let him become this and justifying the horrors he committed in the Emperor's name and after it. A study of a brother who saw too clearly and chose the dark.",
